DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,3,1);
$top = random(3,9,2);
$bot = random(2,8,2);
$ans1 = "1/sqrt($a)";
$ans2 = "$top/$bot";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 8:
$BR $SPACE $BR
Is the function below exponential? $BR $SPACE $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\(  \displaystyle K(x)= \frac{$top^x}{\sqrt{$a} \cdot $bot^x} \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
If so, write the function in the form \( K(x)=ab^x \) and enter the values you find for \( a \) and \( b \) in the indicated blanks below.  If the function is NOT EXPONENTIAL, enter $BBOLD NONE $EBOLD in BOTH blanks below.
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
\( a = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \( \ \ \ \ \ \ \) and \( b = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

END_TEXT


ANS(fun_cmp($ans1,vars=>['N','O','E']) );
ANS(fun_cmp($ans2,vars=>['N','O','E']) );

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
Yes, \( K(x) \) is exponential.  It can be rewritten in standard form as $BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE 
\( K(x) = \frac{$top^x}{\sqrt{$a} \cdot $bot^x} = \left( \frac{1}{\sqrt{$a}} \right) \cdot \left( \frac{$top^x}{$bot^x} \right) = \left( \frac{1}{\sqrt{$a}} \right) \big( \frac{$top}{$bot} \big)^x \) $BR
So \( a = \frac{1}{\sqrt{$a}} \ \) and \( \ b = \frac{$top}{$bot} \).
$BR
END_SOLUTION


ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.